import pandas as pd
import math
import numpy as np
import scipy.special as sc
np.seterr(all='raise')
sc.seterr(all='raise')

repo = pd.read_csv("repo.csv", index_col="id")
repo["url"] = repo["url"].apply(lambda s: s.split("/")[-1])

bench_csv = pd.read_csv("bench.csv")
edges_csv = pd.read_csv("edges.csv", index_col="id")

bench_csv = bench_csv.groupby(["edge_id", "type"]).mean()
bench_csv = bench_csv.unstack(-1)
bench_csv.columns = bench_csv.columns.map(lambda x: x[1])
for col in bench_csv.columns:
    if any(bench_csv[col] == np.nan):
        raise Exception()

bench_csv["singleRTA(online)"] = bench_csv.apply(lambda x: x["singleOffline"] + x["singleRTA"], axis=1)
bench_csv["sepRTA(online)"] = bench_csv.apply(lambda x: x["sepOffline"] + x["sepRTA"], axis=1)
bench_csv["sepORTA(online)"] = bench_csv.apply(lambda x: x["sepOffline"] + x["sepORTA"], axis=1)
bench_csv = bench_csv.drop(columns=["sepORTA", "sepRTA", "singleRTA"])
bench_csv.columns = ["runAll", "sepRTA(offline)", "singleRTA(offline)", "singleRTA(online)", "sepRTA(online)", "sepORTA(online)"]
bench_csv /= 1000

selection = []
for index, row in edges_csv.iterrows():
    tests = set(x for x in row["all_tests"].split(",") if len(x) > 0)
    
    def toset(name):
        value = row[name]
        if not isinstance(value, str):
            return set()
        else:
            return set(x for x in row[name].split(",") if x in tests)
        
    sep = toset("sep_selected")
    single = toset("single_selected")
    hyrts = toset("hyRTS_selected")
    selection.append([index, len(tests), len(single), len(sep), len(hyrts - single), len(hyrts - sep)])

selection = pd.DataFrame(selection, columns = ["id", "total", "single", "sep", "missed_single", "missed_sep"]).set_index("id")

edges = edges_csv.loc[:, ["repo_id", "single_edge_count", "sep_dups_count", "single_dups_count"]]
edges.columns = ["repo_id", "single_edge", "sep_dups", "single_dups"]
edges = edges.join(bench_csv).join(selection)
edges["has_dup"] = edges["single_dups"] > 0

from scipy import stats

RQ1 = edges.loc[:, ["runAll"]]
total_sum = edges.loc[:, ["repo_id", "single", "sep", "missed_single", "missed_sep", "total"]].groupby("repo_id").sum()
for column in ["single", "sep", "missed_single", "missed_sep"]:
    x = total_sum.loc[:, [column, "total"]]
    x["calced"] = x.apply(lambda x: np.round(x[column] / x["total"] * 100, 2), axis=1)
    x = x.drop(columns=["total", column])
    x.columns = [column]
    RQ1 = RQ1.join(x)
    
total_sum = edges.loc[:, ["repo_id", "singleRTA(offline)", "sepRTA(offline)", "singleRTA(online)", "sepRTA(online)", "runAll"]].groupby("repo_id").sum()
for column in ["singleRTA(offline)", "sepRTA(offline)", "singleRTA(online)", "sepRTA(online)"]:
    x = total_sum.loc[:, [column, "runAll"]]
    x["calced"] = x.apply(lambda x: np.round(x[column] / x["runAll"] * 100, 2), axis=1)
    x = x.drop(columns=["runAll", column])
    x.columns = [column]
    RQ1 = RQ1.join(x)
    
p_header.join(RQ1.drop(columns=["runAll"])).drop(columns=["head"]).set_index("pid")

In [24]:
from scipy import stats
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

f, axes = plt.subplots(30, 2, figsize=(25,240,))
col = 0
for repo_id, data in edges.groupby("repo_id"):
    for idx, columns in enumerate([("single", "sep",), ("missed_single", "missed_sep",)]):
        a, b = columns
        row = data[a] - data[b]
        if not all(row == 0):
            pvalue = stats.shapiro(row)[1]
            if pvalue > 0.01:
                print(repo_id, columns)
            else:
                stats.probplot(row, plot=axes[col][idx])
    col += 1
plt.show()

from scipy import stats
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

selected = []
missed = []
for repo_id, data in edges.groupby("repo_id"):
    for idx, columns in enumerate([("single", "sep", selected,)]):
        a, b, result = columns
        try:
            pv = stats.wilcoxon(data[a], data[b])[1]
        except ValueError:
            pv = 1
            
        result.append([repo_id, pv < 0.05])

from scipy import stats
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

f, axes = plt.subplots(30, 2, figsize=(25,240,))
col = 0

for repo_id, data in edges.loc[:, ["repo_id", "singleRTA(online)", "sepRTA(online)", "singleRTA(offline)", "sepRTA(offline)"]].groupby("repo_id"):
    for idx, columns in enumerate([("singleRTA(offline)", "sepRTA(offline)",), ("singleRTA(online)", "sepRTA(online)",)]):
        a, b = columns
        row = data[a] - data[b]
        if not all(row == 0):
            pvalue = stats.shapiro(row)[1]
            if pvalue > 0.01:
                print(repo_id, columns)
                
            stats.probplot(row, plot=axes[col][idx])
    col += 1
plt.show()

from scipy import stats
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

f, axes = plt.subplots(10, 3, figsize=(25,80,))
idx = 0

for repo_id, data in edges.loc[:, ["repo_id", "sepRTA(online)", "sepORTA(online)"]].groupby("repo_id"):
    a, b = ("sepRTA(online)", "sepORTA(online)",)
    row = data[a] - data[b]
    if not all(row == 0):
        pvalue = stats.shapiro(row)[1]
        if pvalue > 0.01:
            print(repo_id)

    stats.probplot(row, plot=axes[idx // 3][idx % 3])
    idx += 1
plt.show()
